What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm most interested in the factors that affects a loan's outcome status

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I believe that most influentiatl features to affect Loan status has to be in those feature (EmploymentStatus, StatedMonthlyIncome, ProsperScore, ProsperRating, Orinigal Loan amount, Term,LP_customerPrincipalPayements )

I expect that either ProsperScore or Prosper Rating would give us an intial insgiht on the Loan status. While the other features will not be directly correlated to the Loan staus, thoough a combination of those features may be insightful to predict the loan status

Multivariate Exploration¶

Create plots of three or more variables to investigate the data even further.

First let's define a function that will automatibcally make the encoded plot for us then let's investigate the combination of our numeric variables from the bivarient plot

In [117]:
def plot_encoder(data,x,y,marker,spec_col):
    '''
    the function is used to make scatter plots 
    note taht x,y, and spec_col have to be strigns and represents col names in data
    x and y has to be numeric 
    marker should be a list consists of two elements 1. the value in spec_col that u want to plot 2. marker shape to be ploted  
    '''
    dummy=data[data[spec_col]==marker[0]]
    plt.scatter(data=dummy,x=x,y=y,marker=marker[1],alpha=0.5);
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.ylabel(y)
